## Introduction

Losartan ({{ drug.molecular_formula }}) is a non peptide, orally active, and selective angiotensin II Type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist drug used mainly to treat hypertension associated with heart failure or renal impairment. It differs from angiotensin-converting enzyme ({{ drug.molecular_formula }}) inhibitors by producing direct antagonism II receptors.1; 2LOS is well absorbed following {{ drug.route_of_administration }} administration with an {{ drug.route_of_administration }} bioavailability of about 33% and reaches peak serum levels in 1.0 h. It undergoes significant rst-pass metabolism to produce an active 5-carboxylic acid metabolite, designated as {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-3174, which is mediated by cytochrome P450 enzymes {{ drug.molecular_formula }} and {{ drug.molecular_formula }}. This metabolite is a long-acting (up to 24 h), noncompetitive antagonist at the AT1receptor and contributes to the pharmacological effects of {{ drug.molecular_formula }}. It is 10{40 times more potent in blocking AT1receptors than the parent drug.3Hydrochlorothiazide ({{ drug.molecular_formula }}) is a popular diuretic of the thiazide class that reduces plasma volume by increasing the excretion of sodium, chloride, and water. The decrease in plasma volume results in counter-regulatory stimulation of the rennin-angiotensin system and the sympathetic nervous system.4Thus, the complimentary action of an angiotensin II receptor antagonist and a thiazide has led to their extensive use in the treatment of Correspondence: pranavshrivastav@yahoo.com714 {{ drug.molecular_formula }} et al./Turk J Chempatients with overt heart failure. Clinical studies have demonstrated antihypertensive efficacy and tolerability ofLOS-{{ drug.molecular_formula }} combination therapy in patients with moderate-to-severe essential hypertension, which is otherwise inadequately controlled by mono drug therapy.5;6Thus, with the advancement of medical science, there is an immense role of combination therapy with multiple drugs or at least two drugs having different modes of action in the treatment of hypertension.7Several methods are reported for the quantitation of {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, alone.

